# Chart Visualization Style

Always use this style when generating matplotlib charts:

## Font & Text
- **Font family**: Calibri
- **All text bold** (font.weight: bold, axes.titleweight: bold, axes.labelweight: bold)
- Title: fontsize 20, color #2d2d2d
- Subtitle: fontsize 12, color #888888
- Axis labels: fontsize 12, color #444444
- Tick labels: fontsize 10, color #444444

## Colors
- **Background**: Creamy `#faf6f1` (both figure and axes)
- **Tableau palette**: `["#4e79a7", "#f28e2b", "#59a14f", "#e15759"]`
- **Gridlines**: `#e0dbd5`, horizontal only, linewidth 0.8
- **Spines**: Remove top and right; left and bottom set to `#cccccc`

## Lines & Markers
- Hollow circle markers (markerfacecolor = background color)
- Default lines: linewidth 2.2, markersize 5, markeredgewidth 1.8, alpha 0.45
- **Current/focus series**: linewidth 4.5, markersize 9, markeredgewidth 3.0, alpha 1.0, higher zorder
- Cumulative totals annotated at end of line in matching color, bold

## Layout
- figsize (20, 8), legend frameless, no tick marks (length=0)
- Save as PNG with dpi=180, facecolor=cream, edgecolor=none
- Open chart externally with `Start-Process` (not inside Cursor)
